# The `ReexportsGenerator` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/reexportsgenerator">ReexportsGenerator</a> can be used with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib/#ae89dfebe97fc65907c1b9194aafe1ade">JITDylib::addGenerator</a> to automatically re-export a subset of the source <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>&#39;s symbols in the target. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/reexportsgenerator">ReexportsGenerator</a> can be used with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib/#ae89dfebe97fc65907c1b9194aafe1ade">JITDylib::addGenerator</a> to automatically re-export a subset of the source <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>&#39;s symbols in the target.

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::orc::ReexportsGenerator::ReexportsGenerator (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> &amp; SourceJD, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a7cb1d8cb0ab2329f032d69d79498c81d">JITDylibLookupFlags</a> SourceJDLookupFlags, <a href="#a6a5a555694e752e5767fc52c805792a7">SymbolPredicate</a> Allow=<a href="#a6a5a555694e752e5767fc52c805792a7">SymbolPredicate</a>())</>}>
Create a reexports generator.

If an Allow predicate is passed, only symbols for which the predicate returns true will be reexported. If no Allow predicate is passed, all symbols will be exported.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h/#l01946">1946</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/core-h">Core.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp/#l00592">592</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/orc/core-cpp">Core.cpp</a>.

## Public Member Functions

### tryToGenerate() {#a9b1cc5b369f4fd3e04b66035eea7c481}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::orc::ReexportsGenerator::tryToGenerate (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/lookupstate">LookupState</a> &amp; LS, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#ac17672ae6b70c781cc77713e88d698eb">LookupKind</a> K, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> &amp; JD, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a7cb1d8cb0ab2329f032d69d79498c81d">JITDylibLookupFlags</a> JDLookupFlags, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbollookupset">SymbolLookupSet</a> &amp; LookupSet)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
DefinitionGenerators should override this method to insert new definitions into the parent <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

K specifies the kind of this lookup. JD specifies the target <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> being searched, and JDLookupFlags specifies whether the search should match against hidden symbols. Finally, Symbols describes the set of unresolved symbols and their associated lookup flags.
